76561198260473981,Recommended,498570,24747456,"Posted: 6 August, 2016",all,awesome vindicator,"Completely unrealistic, it was all going well, until an objective told me to place a pallet on top of a shipping container...in real life this would be COMPLETELY UNVIABLE, the maximum load bearing weight of a shipping container in this configuration far less than the average weight of a forklift truck (3950kg) such as the type seen in the game, the shipping container would collapse injuring the driver and damaging the machine and its load.... not only that but the forklift truck has no tilt control and make unusual sounds NOT inline with the sounds produced by a gas powered forklift truck.its appauling that such an innacurate portrayal of forkliftsmanship could be found here on steam... not to mention the sombraro hat used to customize the players avatar. a sombraro hat such as this goes completely against the ""The Construction (Head Protection) Regulations 1989"" which states. *ahem* ""If a risk assessment has identified the possibility of head injury, then hard hats are mandatory – regardless of the nature of the work, or the size of the project.""ergo you can plainly see the need to a hard hat is required when working in, on, or around a forklift truck...one more point, ""forklicious"" is NOT a real word.in all fairness it IS a pretty fun game and well worth the tiny price. grats to the developer."
