76561198021868661,Recommended,498570,24810213,"Posted: 10 August, 2016",all,Insomnia'77,"Where is the goddamn tilt!?Graphics: 80%Audio: 80%Gameplay: 50%Replayability: 20%Value for money: 100%Overall: 66%I picked this up late at night, thinking ""heck, I'll bite"". And I was surprised in a positive way. This simulator/game is actually a little bit fun. But it could have been so much more, if they put a little more time and effort into it.Graphics and audio is allright. The soundeffects is ok, and the single tune is catchy. They could have added a couple of tunes more, but I doubt most of the owners of this game will play past a couple of hours. There could have been some more details, for example a bit more shelves, and trucks/trains to load the pallets onto. The elevators could have been detailed to something more than just a moving slab.Controls are ok with keyboard. But I guess it is better played with an analog gamepad, as you tend to do a 360 with the keyboard. I am looking forward trying this with a steering wheel, though! The general gameplay is a bit lacking, though. After a while, you're just playing to get the achivements. As I pointed out about the graphics, if they detailed the area a bit more, with more shelves, and different things to load onto, it would have been a lot more interesting. Filled shelves with multiple pallets, and all moveable would have been nice. The ability to cause total havoc by making the shelf fall over would be even more hillarious. But what can you expect from a $1.5 game?And what's up with a forklift with side-shift but no tilt? I had to drive backwards down the steep ramps so I did not lose the pallet."
